UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellant, v. STATE OF ALASKA, Defendant-Appellee. No. 73-2400. United States Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. July 28, 1975. *1377Edward F. Bradley, Jr., Atty. (argued), Lands & Natural Resources Div., Dept. of Justice, Washington, D. C., for plaintiff-appellant. Thomas M. Phillips (argued), Houston, Tex., Charles K. Cranston (argued), Anchorage, Alaska, for defendant-appellee.

Before KOELSCH, CARTER and WALLACE, Circuit Judges.

ORDER

The judgment of the district court is reversed and the case is remanded for further proceedings consistent with United States v. Alaska, - U.S. -, 95 S.Ct. 2240, 45 L.Ed.2d 109 (1975).
